Use shorthands where possible. Examples include:
- object structuring / destructuring
- .length check `if (x.length)` is better than `if (x.length > 0)`
Prefer expressions. Use the ternary operator, but no nested ternaries.
Everyone can read code here, so no need for comments that are 1:1 with what's happening below. An exmaple to avoid
// Re-export from mocks/testEmployee.ts
export { addTestEmployee } from 'mocks/testEmployee.ts'